<p>We don't actually need a form, but now we can put a button inside and this will
<em>POST</em> up to our server. I don't always do this right, but since this action will
<em>change</em> something on the server, it's best done with a POST request. Add a few
classes for styling and say "Cancel Subscription".</p>
<p>I still need to set the <code>action</code> attribute to some URL... but we need to create
that endpoint first!</p>
<p>Open <code>ProfileController</code>. This file renders the account page, but we're also going
to put code in here to handle some other things on this page, like cancelling a
subscription and updating your credit card.</p>
<p>Create a new <code>public function cancelSubscriptionAction()</code>. Give this a URL:
<code>@Route("/profile/subscription/cancel")</code> and a name: <code>account_subscription_cancel</code>:</p>
